    <div xml:id="PN316-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. maturaikkaḷḷiṟkaṭaiyattaṉ
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN316">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kaḷḷiṉ vāḻttik kaḷḷiṉ vāḻttik</l>
<l>kāṭṭoṭu miṭainta cīyā muṉṟi</l>
<l>ṉāṭceruk kaṉantart tuñcu vōṉē</l>
<l>yavaṉem miṟaivaṉ yāmavaṉ pāṇar</l>
<l>nerunai vanta viruntiṟku maṟṟuttaṉ</l>
<l>ṉirumpuṭaip paḻavāḷ vaittaṉa ṉiṉṟik</l>
<l>karuṅkōṭṭuc cīṟiyāḻ paṇaiya mitukoṇ</l>
<l>ṭīvati lāḷa ṉeṉṉātu nīyum</l>
<l>vaḷḷi maruṅkul vayaṅkiḻai yaṇiyak</l>
<l>kaḷḷuṭaik kalattēm yāmakiḻ tūṅkac</l>
<l>ceṉṟuvāy civantumēl varuka</l>
<l>ciṟukaṇ yāṉai vēntuviḻu muṟavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Praising the toddy, praising the toddy,</l>
<l>he is the one sleeping in stupor from the day's pressings</l>
<l>in the unswept front yard set closely to the wilderness.</l>
<l>He is our lord. We are his bards.</l>
<l>For the guest, again, who came yesterday</l>
<l>he put down the old sword from [his] large side. Today</l>
<l>we are pawning this black-necked little lute. Taking it,</l>
<l>without saying “He is a man who does not give!”, you too</l>
<l>go, mouth reddened [and] come back</l>
<l>so that [those with] glowing jewels adorn [their] vine-[thin] waists,</l>
<l>while we sway in delight, with toddy in our pots,</l>
<l>since the king on a small-eyed elephant is in distress.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
